				\begin{document}$$0.6\%$$\end{document}0.6% (red line in Fig. 6a). The blue line is obtained from system (1) with no vaccination control. The green line is obtained from system (1) when the vaccination strategy (15) is applied. Because vaccination has been implemented, the number of people cured by treatment will become very small (Fig. 6b). Most susceptible gain immunity directly through vaccination and do not need treatment. This shows that vaccination can greatly reduce the burden on medical facilities.

